secondaryOutcomes.description:
The secondary aim is to estimate the prevalence of low antidepressant adherence, as well as associated maternal factors.

This will be done through the following specific objectives:

1. assessment of the psychometric properties of the AADP scale and identification of cut-off levels for low and high adherence to antidepressants in pregnancy;
2. description of the extent to which women adhere to antidepressants in pregnancy;
3. determination of the maternal factors associated with low adherence to antidepressants during pregnancy.
